  "title": "Software Developer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements\tRole Overview</p><p></p><p>We are looking for a motivated and detail-oriented Junior Java Developer to join our development team. The ideal candidate should have a strong foundation in Java programming and a basic understanding of Spring Boot to support the design, development, testing, and maintenance of backend applications. This is an excellent opportunity for freshers or early-career developers to grow in a collaborative, learning-focused environment.</p><p></p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>•Assist in the development and maintenance of Java-based applications using Spring Boot.</p><p>•Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code following best practices.</p><p>•Support the development of RESTful APIs and backend services.</p><p>•Participate in requirement analysis, design discussions, and daily stand-ups.</p><p>•Debug, test, and fix application issues to ensure performance and reliability.</p><p>•Work closely with senior developers, QA, and product teams.</p><p>•Contribute to code reviews and continuous improvement initiatives.</p><p></p><p>Required Skills & Qualifications</p><p></p><p>•Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related field (or equivalent practical experience).</p><p>•Strong fundamentals in Core Java (OOP, Collections, Multithreading basics, Exception Handling).</p><p>•Basic hands-on knowledge of Spring Boot and Spring Framework.</p><p>•Understanding of REST APIs, HTTP concepts, and MVC architecture.</p><p>•Familiarity with SQL and any relational database (MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc.).</p><p>•Basic knowledge of Git or any version control system.</p><p>•Good problem-solving skills and eagerness to learn new technologies.</p><p></p>",
